From the gate there is a problem here: there is a definite (but thankfully not hostile) schism between those who prefer their anthros very heavily based off of their real life counterparts in behavior and physiology, and others who are just after "people that happen to be animals."

You can sling around some ideas about how certain species act, and how they're perceived by society in mass, but asking people to stick to a setting is a touch unfair. Especially if their preferred species might be problematic in some way and they have to come up with some convoluted reason to explain why they're in a relationship when all they want to do is imagine holding hands with a komodo dragon in the park without any fuss. I can already see the "pets: slavery, caste, or career?" arguments from here, too.

Also creating a setting in general needs a lot of fine touching and minding of details, and a solid foundation that every can agree on that isn't just the fetish at hand. That's how you end up with things like futadom worlds (and our older cousin /PoFg/), where everything feels super hamfisted while reading it because the fetish came first instead of reasoning. If the answer for any question of "But why" regarding a key feature in the setting is "Because the fetish," then we're already off to a shit start. As it stands, we're only here to see human dudes have sex with animal chicks. More structure is not exactly needed at the moment, and writefags don't seem to be comparing notes with each other to maintain consistency.

Would it neat? Maybe. It would definitely be something to point do as an example of what /hmofa/ expects and is interested in, enough to act like a cheat sheet for newcomers. But if it's done poorly it'll just be another shitty fetish setting hold together by hazard tape and day old jizz. And the last thing we need is some autist shitposting at new OC because 'it doesn't fit with the setting, so it doesn't belong here/is shit'

The idea was if you had a setting with both humans and anthros but the humans still have the same relative intelligence to the anthros as we do to normal animals as well as the same general kind of relationship.
This would Humans the setting's version of the True Fae and when you consider what domesticated animals are and how a wild animal must see them (pic related was a very big inspiration in that regard) then that only compounds the similarity.

I wrote up a longer version but the basic gist of things is
>Futuristic super advanced humans with magic like technology find the ruins of old earth
>Decide to return life to it (and unintentionally create "magic" through all the nanites they leave behind)
>End up creating all sorts of wild stuff that's nothing like the original earth biosphere including uplifted bipedal animals
>Most get bored and fuck off back to space but some decide to stay so they can live as gods over these new primitive but sentient life forms
>Unfortunately for them there's a lot of junk in orbit and under the ground the engineers didn't pay much attention to
>Including a bunch of dormant super AIs that are now finally waking up in response to all the new life
>The AIs mistake the anthros for humans and the humans for some external invader because of the tech difference
>Many anthros start worshipping the AIs as gods
>Most of the AIs are designed to run corporations and mistake this new religion as a consumer base and start hiring (making priests) and start upping security (wage war with the humans)
>Humans are mostly civvies and scientists not military so even with the tech difference the AIs and their "angels" (old ass murder robots) push them back
>Humans now live in the shadows of the world far from the "gods" prying eyes where they live out their fucked up hedonistic lives kidnapping anthros and mutating them to serve their purposes

Surface level the setting would be fairly medieval fantasy with a bit of schizo tech.
